\noindent Figure 2. 
Identification of the results of all possible measurements of the
coordinates of the particle for each of the stationary states
$|p;\T\ra$ of $W(p)$  with $p=2$.  
For $q=0$ or $q=1$ (the states on the first and the second
line from the top), the coordinates of the particle correspond to 
one of the eight nests on the sphere, indicated by circles. 
For $q=2$ (the bottom line), there are three independent lowest
energy states. For these states, there are only 4 possible nests on each sphere with
radius $\sqrt{2}$. These 4 nests are in the $r_1r_2$-plane for $\T=(1,1,0)$, in the
$r_1r_3$-plane for $\T=(1,0,1)$, and in the $r_2r_3$-plane for $\T=(0,1,1)$.


